fullDescription.markdown:
Reports an object property that can be converted to ES6 shorthand style and provides a quick-fix to do it.

Example:


    var obj = {foo:foo}

After applying the quick-fix the code looks as follows:


    var obj = {foo}

Inspection ID: ES6ShorthandObjectProperty

fullDescription.text:
Reports access to outer mutable variables from functions. Example: 'for (var i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    setTimeout(function() {
        console.log(i); // bad
    }, 0);
  }' Inspection ID: JSReferencingMutableVariableFromClosure

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports access to outer mutable variables from functions.

Example:


