fullDescription.text:
Reports a bitwise mask expression which for sure evaluates to 'true' or 'false'. Expressions are of the form '(var & constant1) == constant2' or '(var | constant1) == constant2', where 'constant1' and 'constant2' are incompatible bitmask constants. Example: '// Incompatible mask: as the last byte in mask is zero,
// something like 0x1200 would be possible, but not 0x1234
if ((mask & 0xFF00) == 0x1234) {...}' Inspection ID: IncompatibleMaskJS

fullDescription.markdown:
Reports a bitwise mask expression which for sure evaluates to `true` or `false`. Expressions are of the form `(var & constant1) == constant2` or `(var | constant1) == constant2`, where `constant1` and `constant2` are incompatible bitmask constants.

Example:


    // Incompatible mask: as the last byte in mask is zero,
