For more information about closures and goroutines, refer to [What happens
with closures running as goroutines? at go.dev](https://go.dev/doc/faq#closures_and_goroutines).

Example:

    for _, v := range []string{"a", "b", "c"} {
      go func() {
        fmt.Println(v) // output will likely be `c c c`, not `a b c`
      }()
    }

After the quick-fix is applied:

